<br>
I was approached by several clerics. They wanted to know my views on the Ragefire list that has been set up on Quellious. I first started reading about this list a month ago. I've read, I've talked to clerics and I've thought about the pros and cons of this list.<br>
<br>
I have decided...I think this list is wrong. Also I know several Clerics that think this list is wrong. I also know several Guilds that think this list is wrong. I am hoping that that they post and tell you their feelings on this matter.<br>
<br>
I joined the cleric chat channel Saturday and tried to start a discussion about my qualms with the list. I was immediately threatened with...we dont care if you like it...we have the force, so you cant ks us. During the course of this discussion I was told that if I fought this list my reputation and the reputation of my guild would be damaged. When the people on the chat channel found out they couldnt intimidate me then the chat became  a little more civalized. I kept reiterating that I wasnt there to threaten them but to discuss the list.<br>
<br>
This list, although well intentioned, it is unfair. The  requirements to get on the list are ridiculous and humiliating to the cleric wanting on the list. Do you realize that in order for a cleric to get on this list they have to sit in Skyfire for 6 hours (I know someone who was made to do this) to prove their worthiness to be on the list. I am here to tell you I dont have to prove my worthiness to any one on this server. I'm not quite sure why the people controling the list feel this is nessecary. Every reason I come up with is very insulting so I wont post them.<br>
<br>
This list goes against Verant's rules. Quellioius is a FFA Server. This was stated when the lists for Fear and Hate were gotten rid of.<br>
<br>
I see several people on the list from the same guild. I see several people on the list who have at least one or more charactors that already have epics. <br>
<br>
But the main reason this list is unfair...not everyone had the same oportunity to get on the list at the same time. I keep hearing it would have been imposible to tell every cleric on the server about the list. Let me ask you ... did you tell your guild about the list and your friends about the list? So your friends and guild are probably on the list.<br>
<br>
Also, I dont see the Ragefire spawn being any different than any other epic spawn. They dont do this for Faye, they dont do this for the dragans, i can't think of any other epic spawn this done for. So why Rage.<br>
<br>
I was also told that &quot;all&quot; the big guilds support this list. I have talked to a big guild, and I have been told that two other big guilds don't support this list. So that is three what I consider big guilds that dont support this list.<br>
<br>
I am going to recommend that my Guild not follow this list. If two or more clerics want to camp rage then it can be petitioned or go by what ever the correct Vernant sanctioned rules are.<br>
<br>
To ask people, that didn't know about the list at its inception to wait until March or April of next year to fight Rage Fire is ridiculous.<br>
<br>
For those of you who think this is sour grapes...I have my epic. I have had it for a year now. That is why I am posting, the clerics without their epics are being intimidated by the people running the list. These arent my words but the words of the clerics talking to me.<br>
<br>
Please post your feelings pro or con...<br>
<br>
Just trying to let you know what is going on.<br>
<br>
Yinta<br>
60th Epic Cleric<br>
Gray Soldiers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugypsysongman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gypsy Songman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Drunken Lout</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/11/02 11:41:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.houston.rr.com/neuromt/pwned.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> 3 quick things, cause I'm tired.<br>
<br>
1. Do not claim to be the representative of the downtrodden without being able to produce at least a few of said downtrodden. I (nor, I imagine, anyone else) will take your word for it.<br>
<br>
2. This list came to be because Rage was the most contested spawn in the game, bar none. KS'ing and backstabbing was frequent. There are not many people who are willing to see it go back to that- myself amongst them. I have put myself at the service of any cleric that's camping Rage in accodance with the list before, and will remind them that it's an option now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
3. VI's policy is 'First sufficient force in zone'- IE, if you've got the people there to kill it, it's yours. You will be hard pressed to beat the mobilization of a good chunk of the guilds on the server to get Rage first.<br>
<br>
I respect your forwardness, and I agree the list isn't perfect. But it's the best we've come up with, and that's all there is to it. It might suck, but it's better than camping Rage for a month and getting your spawn KS'd every time. <p>Lauriston Pianoforte<br>That Guy<br>Bard of Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ururarksoulhunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rurark Soulhunter</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/12/02 12:03:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> To anyone that is not a cleric out there think what you would do if your last epic piece was a 9 month waiting list.  A list that has secondary characters on it for sure, and most likely people who are not even to that point yet.  Personally I would not like that fact one bit, and would not stand for such a list.  Ragefire is the higest contested spawn in game, and that is no players fault, but to make clerics who just want there epic wait on a list for over 8 months when secondary characters are ahead of them is rediculous.  <br>
