<br>
So, is the list as it is more fair that the situation prior to the list?  In my opinion, no, it isn't.  People found out about the list at varying times and the people who decide who goes on the list at this point are people who are already on the list.  In my opinion a list setup as this one has been was at the least unfair at it's inception and at the worst screaming<br>
for abuse in it's continued use.<br>
<br>
Prior to the list RF was a poorly conceived step in the cleric epic quest (well, I suppose after the list as well :*)  ).  However, the rules regarding it were layed out by VI and everybody on the server had equal access to those rules at the same time.  With the list, a subset of the server made rules of it's own, then expected the rest of the server<br>
to follow those rules regardless of when they learn about them.  To ensure that threatens to KS any RF from a cleric not on the list trying to take it (I can't help but say, note the irony here, we're sick of people KSing RF, so we're going to establish our own rules, and anybody who doesn't like them we KS).<br>
<br>
However well intentioned the list was at it's start, I honestly don't think it's better than RF was.<br>
<br>
And as a side note, /rude Verant for creating this whole mess in the first place. :*/<br>
